Chinese Cai Yun/Fu Haifeng win men's doubles badminton Olympic gold
2012-08-05 15:20:21 GMT
LONDON, Aug. 5 (Xinhua) -- Chinese badminton players Cai Yun and Fu Haifeng beat their Danish rivals 2-0 Sunday afternoon and clinched the gold medal in the men's doubles of the Olympic Games in the Wembley Arena.This means Chinese sweep all the badminton gold medals produced at the London Olympics.Mathias Boe and Carsten Mogensen from Denmark won the silver, while the bronze fell into pockets of Jung Jae Sung and Lee Yong Dae from South Korea.
